Label: SNORD115@
Comment: SNORD115 primarily regulates alternate splicing of HTR2C pre-mRNA, by binding to the latter.</br>Alternate splicing and adenosine-to-inosine RNA-editing both lead to translation of less functional receptors.</br>Loss of SNORD115 might influence 5-HT2CR regulated appetite, and could therefore contribute to hyperphagia in PWS.
